    "It indicates that the second order non-equilibrium (∆ 2,xx M 5,1 ∆ (1) mn ∆ (2) mn ∆ 2,xx ∆ (2) 2,xx ∆ (1) 2,xx ∆ (2) 2,xx /∆ (1) 2,xx ∆ (2) 2,xx ∆ 2,xx ∆ (2) 2,xx /∆ (1) 2,xx) cannot be ignored compared with the first order non-equilibrium (), that is, the relative non-equilibrium strength is larger.",
